Lastly, s_1=n_1-n_0=2-0=2.  Since s_2=s_1, we again have a trivial R_1 and need only complete our basis by evaluating the basis vectors of Z_2 with T, 
                \vect{z}_{1,1}&=\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{2,1}}=A\vect{z}_{2,1}=\colvector{1\\1\\0\\1\\1\\1}
                &
                \vect{z}_{1,2}&=\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{2,2}}=A\vect{z}_{2,2}=\colvector{-2\\-2\\-5\\-2\\-1\\0}
              Now we reorder these vectors as the desired basis,B=\set{
            \vect{z}_{1,1},\,\vect{z}_{2,1},\,\vect{z}_{3,1},\,\vect{z}_{4,1},\,\vect{z}_{1,2},\,\vect{z}_{2,2}}

We now apply  to build a matrix representation of T relative to B,
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{1,1}}}&=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{1,1}}=\vectrep{B}{\zerovector}=\colvector{0\\0\\0\\0\\0\\0}
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{2,1}}}&=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{2,1}}=\vectrep{B}{\vect{z}_{1,1}}=\colvector{1\\0\\0\\0\\0\\0}
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{3,1}}} &=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{3,1}}=\vectrep{B}{\vect{z}_{2,1}}=\colvector{0\\1\\0\\0\\0\\0}
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{4,1}}} &=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{4,1}}=\vectrep{B}{\vect{z}_{3,1}}=\colvector{0\\0\\1\\0\\0\\0}
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{1,2}}} &=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{1,2}}=\vectrep{B}{\zerovector}=\colvector{0\\0\\0\\0\\0\\0}
                \vectrep{B}{\lteval{T}{\vect{z}_{2,2}}}&=\vectrep{B}{A\vect{z}_{2,2}}=\vectrep{B}{\vect{z}_{1,2}}=\colvector{0\\0\\0\\0\\1\\0}
